{
  "Question": "<blockquote> <p>Question: Suppose <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_670\"><math alttext=\"f:(-\\delta,\\delta)\\to(0,\\infty)\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>f</mi><mo>:</mo><mrow><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>\u03b4</mi></mrow><mo>,</mo><mi>\u03b4</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><mo>\u2192</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u221e</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mrow></mrow></semantics></math></span> has the property that <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_671\"><math alttext=\"\\lim_{x\\to 0}\\left(f(x)+\\frac{1}{f(x)}\\right)=2.\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mrow><msub><mo>lim</mo><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>\u2192</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub><mo>\u2061</mo><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><mrow><mi>f</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mi>f</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mrow></mfrac></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow><mo>.</mo></mrow></semantics></math></span> Show that <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_672\"><math alttext=\"\\lim_{x\\to 0}f(x)=1\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mrow><msub><mo>lim</mo><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>\u2192</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub><mo>\u2061</mo><mrow><mi>f</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mrow></mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></semantics></math></span>.</p> </blockquote> <p>My approach: Let <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_673\"><math alttext=\"h:(-\\delta,\\delta)\\to(-1,\\infty)\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>h</mi><mo>:</mo><mrow><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>\u03b4</mi></mrow><mo>,</mo><mi>\u03b4</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><mo>\u2192</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u221e</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mrow></mrow></semantics></math></span> be such that <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_674\"><math alttext=\"h(x)=f(x)-1,\\forall x\\in(-\\delta,\\delta).\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mrow><mrow><mi>h</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>=</mo><mrow><mrow><mi>f</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mrow><mo>,</mo><mrow><mrow><mo>\u2200</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow><mo>\u2208</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>\u03b4</mi></mrow><mo>,</mo><mi>\u03b4</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mrow></mrow><mo>.</mo></mrow></semantics></math></span> Note that if we can show that <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_675\"><math alttext=\"\\lim_{x\\to 0}h(x)=0\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mrow><msub><mo>lim</mo><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>\u2192</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub><mo>\u2061</mo><mrow><mi>h</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mrow></mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></semantics></math></span>, then we will be done. Now since we have <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_676\"><math alttext=\"\\lim_{x\\to 0}\\left(f(x)+\\frac{1}{f(x)}\\right)=2\\implies\\lim_{x\\to 0}\\frac{(f(x% )-1)^{2}}{f(x)}=0\\implies\\lim_{x\\to 0}\\frac{h^{2}(x)}{h(x)+1}=0.\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mrow><msub><mo>lim</mo><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>\u2192</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub><mo>\u2061</mo><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><mrow><mi>f</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mi>f</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mrow></mfrac></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>\u27f9</mo><mrow><msub><mo>lim</mo><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>\u2192</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub><mo>\u2061</mo><mfrac><msup><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mrow><mrow><mi>f</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mrow><mi>f</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mrow></mfrac></mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>\u27f9</mo><mrow><msub><mo>lim</mo><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>\u2192</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub><mo>\u2061</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>h</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mrow><mrow><mrow><mi>h</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac></mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow><mo>.</mo></mrow></semantics></math></span> Next I tried to come up with some bounds in order to use Sandwich theorem to show that <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_677\"><math alttext=\"\\lim_{x\\to 0}h(x)=0,\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mrow><msub><mo>lim</mo><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>\u2192</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub><mo>\u2061</mo><mrow><mi>h</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mrow></mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow><mo>,</mo></mrow></semantics></math></span> but the bounds didn't quite work out. The bounds were the following: <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_678\"><math alttext=\"\\begin{cases}h(x)\\geq\\frac{h^{2}(x)}{h(x)+1},\\text{when }h(x)\\geq 0,\\\\ h(x)&lt;\\frac{h^{2}(x)}{h(x)+1},\\text{when }h(x)&lt;0.\\end{cases}\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo>{</mo><mtable columnspacing=\"5pt\" rowspacing=\"0pt\"><mtr><mtd columnalign=\"left\"><mrow><mrow><mrow><mrow><mi>h</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>\u2265</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>h</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mrow><mrow><mrow><mi>h</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac></mrow><mo>,</mo><mrow><mrow><mtext>when\u00a0</mtext><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>h</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>\u2265</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mrow><mo>,</mo></mrow></mtd><mtd></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd columnalign=\"left\"><mrow><mrow><mrow><mrow><mi>h</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>&lt;</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>h</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mrow><mrow><mrow><mi>h</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac></mrow><mo>,</mo><mrow><mrow><mtext>when\u00a0</mtext><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>h</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mrow><mo>.</mo></mrow></mtd><mtd></mtd></mtr></mtable></mrow></semantics></math></span></p> <p>How to proceed after this?</p>",
  "Title": "If <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_668\"><math alttext=\"\\lim_{x\\to 0}\\left(f(x)+\\frac{1}{f(x)}\\right)=2,\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mrow><msub><mo>lim</mo><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>\u2192</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub><mo>\u2061</mo><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><mrow><mi>f</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mi>f</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mrow></mfrac></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow><mo>,</mo></mrow></semantics></math></span> show that <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_669\"><math alttext=\"\\lim_{x\\to 0}f(x)=1\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mrow><msub><mo>lim</mo><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>\u2192</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub><mo>\u2061</mo><mrow><mi>f</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mrow></mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></semantics></math></span>.",
